The paper deals with the problem of Maximum $k$-Vertex Cover, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and optimization. The paper presents an FPT approximation scheme and an efficient approximate kernelization scheme for the problem, which are techniques commonly used in parameterized complexity and computational geometry. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are all likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also discusses an application of the problem outside of parameterized complexity, which suggests a possible connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
